          "imgAlt": "Paragraph 2 illustration",
          "imgPosition": "right",
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "There are forty people on the bus. They come from Britain, America, France, Italy and Holland. At Troy they all have lunch. Then they start to look at the old city. It is a very hot day. After an hour, Mark sits under a tree. “I’m going to stop here for a moment,” he tells Fay. “OK,” she answers. Then Mark sees something on the ground. “What’s that?” he thinks."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
