          "imgAlt": "Paragraph 4 illustration",
          "imgPosition": "right",
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "Ten seconds later the light and the wind stop. Mark opens his eyes. He is standing on a beach. He can see hundreds of ships and men. Behind him there is a beautiful city with high walls. “Where am I?” he thinks. “Where’s my family?” He puts the yellow stone in his pocket. Then one of the men says to him, “Boy! Come here!”"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
