          "imgAlt": "Paragraph 5 illustration",
          "imgPosition": "right",
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "“Me?” Mark walks across the beach to a long, black ship. “Carry this,” the man says. He gives Mark a lot of wood. Then he gets off the ship. “Follow me,” he says. Mark follows him. The man is very tall and has a short, brown beard. “I don’t know your face,” he says. “Are you new here?” “Y-yes,” Mark answers. “That’s right. I’m new here.”"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
