          "imgPosition": "right",
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "They walk down the hill. There are a lot of men workingunder the horse. One of them talks to Andros. “There’s a problem,” he says. “We can’t find a stone for the second eye. We must find one before tomorrow.” Mark looks at the horse’s one bright eye. Then he remembers the stone in his pocket. “Wait!” he says. “I think I can help you.”"
            }
          ]
        }
