              "textEn": "He takes the stone out of his pocket. “But how. . .?!” says Andros. The man smiles. “That’s it. That’s it!” He looks at Mark. “What’s your name, boy?” Mark tells him. “He’s new here,” says Andros. “Ah!” The man is very happy. “Well ... we must thank him. / know. You can come with us in the horse tomorrow night.” Mark’s mouth opens. “Me?!”"
