          "imgPosition": "right",
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "That evening Mark sits near a big fire on the beach. There is an old woman beside him. Her name is Ana and she is a cook. She tells Mark lots of stories. Stories about Greece, the war, and the beautiful princess Helen. In the end she goes to bed. “Goodbye, boy,” she says. “Come and see me again one day. Come and see me again.”"
