          "imgPosition": "right",
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "Next morning the horse is ready. Greek soldiers pull it to the gates of Troy. Then they leave it there, inside the horse there are forty Greeks. They wait all afternoon under the hot, yellow sun. Mark is sitting in the horse’s head. “What happens now?” he thinks. Suddenly the gates open. Trojan soldiers walk out. They pull the horse inside and shut the gates again."
