          "imgPosition": "right",
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "Mark can hear the Trojans. “Why are the Greeks giving us this horse?” asks one. “Do you think they want to end the war?” “Yes! Look!” says a soldier on top of the city walls. “Their ships are leaving!” After that the Trojans eat, sing and dance all evening. Then they go to bed very late and Troy is quiet. At that moment the Greeks climb out of the horse."
